UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2520
1 or reformatory institution, during an escape from imprisonment, or while he or she
2 awaits imprisonment, the sentence imposed for that offense may be added to the
3 portion of the term which remained unserved at the time of the commission of the
4 offense. The sentence imposed upon any person convicted of an escape or
5 attempted escape offense shall run consecutively with any other sentence which the
6 defendant must serve.
7 (4) Notwithstanding any provision in this chapter to the contrary, if a person is
8 convicted of an offense that is committed while he or she is imprisoned in a penal
9 or reformatory institution, the sentence imposed for that offense may, upon order of
10 the trial court, be served in that institution. The person may be transferred to
11 another institution pursuant to administrative regulations of the Department of
12 Corrections.
